The method `hitBricks` returns an array `result` of integers.
The length of the `result` array is equal to the number of rows in the `hits` parameter.
Each element `result[i]` in the `result` array represents the number of bricks that will fall after the `i`th erasure is applied.
The `grid` parameter is not modified by the method.
The `grid` parameter remains in a valid state after the method is executed.
The `result` array does not contain any negative values.
The `result` array does not contain any values greater than the total number of bricks in the `grid` parameter.
